v_n
v_1 = 1(2)(3)\;...\;(1+m) = (m+1)!
v_2 = 2(3)(4)\;...\;(2+m) = \frac{(m+2)!}{1}
v_3 = 3(4)(5)\;...\;(3+m) = \frac{(m+3)!}{2!}
\implies v_n = \frac{(m+n)!}{(n-1)!}
\implies v_{n+1} - v_n = \frac{(m+n+1)!}{n!} - \frac{(m+n)!}{(n-1)!}
